a.title: ― InstanceKey: Single-valued key representation produced from the merge of the representations of all key members and a descriptor.

a.title: ― LongKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a long dataset.

a.title: ― Population: Universe with time and geography specified.

a.xlink:title: ― WideKey: Collection of data instances that uniquely identify a collection of data points in a wide dataset.

a.title: ― CatalogDetails: A set of information useful for attribution, data discovery, and access.

a.title: ― InternationalString: Packaging structure for multiple language versions of the same string content. Where an element of this type is repeatable, the expectation is that each repetition contains different content, each of which can be expressed in multiple languages. The language designation goes on the individual String ...
